@*
    Example 2 — Choosing a strategy.

    Strategy decides whether the native share sheet is preferred over the
    in-page list.

      Auto   (default) — sheet when the browser has one, else the list.
      Native           — always attempt the sheet.
      List             — never attempt it; never even ask.

    Auto is the right default, but it means BEHAVIOUR DIFFERS BY
    PLATFORM: the same button shows the OS sheet on a phone and an
    in-page list on a desktop. That is usually better on each, but your
    help text and support scripts cannot then describe one flow. When
    consistency matters more than native integration — a documented
    workflow, a training video, a screenshot in a manual — pin it to
    List.

    A dismissed sheet ENDS the interaction. It does not fall through to
    the list, because that would resurrect UI the user just dismissed.
    OnNativeShare tells you the sheet was used instead of the list; note
    it does not fire on dismissal, since nothing was shared.
*@

@page "/examples/share-button/strategies"
@rendermode InteractiveServer
@using LilyDesignSystem.Blazor.Helpers

<h2>Auto — native sheet where available</h2>
<ShareButton Label="Share (auto)"
             Targets="@Targets"
             Strategy="ShareStrategy.Auto"
             CopyLabel="Copy link"
             CopiedLabel="Link copied"
             CopyFailedLabel="Could not copy — copy it from the address bar"
             OnNativeShare="@(url => Log($"native sheet used for {url}"))" />

<h2>List — always the in-page list</h2>
<ShareButton Label="Share (list)"
             Targets="@Targets"
             Strategy="ShareStrategy.List"
             CopyLabel="Copy link"
             CopiedLabel="Link copied"
             CopyFailedLabel="Could not copy — copy it from the address bar"
             OnShare="@(args => Log($"chose {args.TargetId}"))" />

<p aria-live="polite">@_last</p>

@code {
    private string _last = "";

    private void Log(string message)
    {
        _last = message;
        StateHasChanged();
    }

    private static readonly ShareTarget[] Targets =
    {
        new()
        {
            Id = "linkedin",
            Label = "LinkedIn",
            Href = (url, _, _) =>
                $"https://www.linkedin.com/sharing/share-offsite/?url={Uri.EscapeDataString(url)}",
        },
        new()
        {
            Id = "reddit",
            Label = "Reddit",
            Href = (url, title, _) =>
                $"https://www.reddit.com/submit?url={Uri.EscapeDataString(url)}&title={Uri.EscapeDataString(title)}",
        },
    };
}
